# P10-001: Filter pushdown (WHERE → reader filters)

Let a `WHERE` clause drive the reader's existing region/frequency/sample/genotype
filters, so `... WHERE CHROM='17' AND POS BETWEEN 43e6 AND 43.1e6` runs the same
targeted scan as `region := '17:43000000-43100000'` — idiomatic SQL instead of
named parameters, and the enabler for efficient ATTACH views (P11-001).

## Status

- [ ] Declare `filter_pushdown = true` on `read_pfile` (and `read_pvar`/`read_pgen` where applicable)
- [ ] Map the pushed `TableFilterSet` to the existing filter backend at bind/init
